The `getColumnTitle` method takes an integer `columnNumber` as input and returns its corresponding column title as a string. It uses a `StringBuilder` to build up the title character by character. The algorithm works by repeatedly taking the remainder of `columnNumber` divided by 26 (since there are 26 letters in the alphabet), appending the corresponding letter to the `StringBuilder`, and then dividing `columnNumber` by 26 (integer division) to move to the next place value. Note that we subtract 1 from `columnNumber` at the start in order to make the algorithm 0-indexed (Excel column numbers start at 1, but our algorithm needs to treat them starting at 0).
